The article is a proclamation by President Barack Obama commemorating the 50th anniversary of the United States Agency for International Development (USAID). USAID was founded in 1961 by President John F. Kennedy and has worked to support developing countries in their efforts to improve their futures. The organization focuses on promoting sustainable growth, good governance, innovation in agriculture, education, and global health, and providing aid in response to natural disasters and humanitarian crises. USAID's efforts have helped many developing countries become stable and prosperous nations. The proclamation highlights the importance of USAID's work and calls on Americans to observe the anniversary with programs and activities that honor the organization and its workers.